defs.docs: A `HashMap` wrapper that holds key-value pairs in insertion order.

defs.name: LinkedHashMap
defs.docs: A linked hash map.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a linked hash map.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs: Creates an empty linked hash map with the given initial capacity.

defs.name: with_hasher
defs.docs: Creates an empty linked hash map with the given initial hash builder.

defs.name: with_capacity_and_hasher
defs.docs: Creates an empty linked hash map with the given initial capacity and hash builder.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more elements to be inserted into the map. The
 map may reserve more space to avoid frequent allocations.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity of the map as much as possible. It will drop down as much as possible
 while maintaining the internal rules and possibly leaving some space in accordance with the
 resize policy.

defs.name: entry
defs.value: fn (&mut self, k: K) -> Entry<K, V, S>
defs.docs: Gets the given key's corresponding entry in the map for in-place manipulation.

defs.name: entries
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator visiting all entries in insertion order.
 Iterator element type is `OccupiedEntry<K, V, S>`. Allows for removal
 as well as replacing the entry.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, k: K, v: V) -> Option<V>
defs.docs:
Inserts a key-value pair into the map. If the key already existed, the old value is
 returned.

defs.name: contains_key
defs.docs: Checks if the map contains the given key.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns the value corresponding to the key in the map.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Returns the mutable reference corresponding to the key in the map.

defs.name: get_refresh
defs.docs: Returns the value corresponding to the key in the map.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes and returns the value corresponding to the key from the map.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Returns the maximum number of key-value pairs the map can hold without reallocating.

defs.name: pop_front
defs.docs: Removes the first entry.

defs.name: front
defs.docs: Gets the first entry.

defs.name: pop_back
defs.docs: Removes the last entry.

defs.name: back
defs.docs: Gets the last entry.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of key-value pairs in the map.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns whether the map is currently empty.

defs.name: hasher
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the map's hasher.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the map of all key-value pairs.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs:
Returns a double-ended iterator visiting all key-value pairs in order of insertion.
 Iterator element type is `(&'a K, &'a V)`

defs.name: iter_mut
defs.docs:
Returns a double-ended iterator visiting all key-value pairs in order of insertion.
 Iterator element type is `(&'a K, &'a mut V)`

 use linked_hash_map::LinkedHashMap;

defs.name: values

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs:
An insertion-order iterator over a `LinkedHashMap`'s entries, with immutable references to the
 values.

defs.name: IterMut
defs.docs:
An insertion-order iterator over a `LinkedHashMap`'s entries, with mutable references to the
 values.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: A consuming insertion-order iterator over a `LinkedHashMap`'s entries.

defs.name: Entries
defs.docs:
An insertion-order iterator over a `LinkedHashMap`'s entries represented as
 an `OccupiedEntry`.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An insertion-order iterator over a `LinkedHashMap`'s keys.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An insertion-order iterator over a `LinkedHashMap`'s values.

defs.name: Occupied
defs.docs: An occupied Entry.

defs.name: Vacant
defs.docs: A vacant Entry.

defs.name: Entry
defs.docs: A view into a single location in a map, which may be vacant or occupied.

defs.name: OccupiedEntry
defs.docs: A view into a single occupied location in a `LinkedHashMap`.

defs.name: VacantEntry
defs.docs: A view into a single empty location in a `LinkedHashMap`.

defs.name: key
defs.docs: Returns the entry key

defs.name: or_insert
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the default if empty, and returns
 a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: or_insert_with
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the result of the default function if empty,
 and returns a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: key
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the entry key

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: into_mut
defs.docs:
Converts the OccupiedEntry into a mutable reference to the value in the entry
 with a lifetime bound to the map itself

defs.name: insert
defs.docs: Sets the value of the entry, and returns the entry's old value

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Takes the value out of the entry, and returns it

defs.name: key
